messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, I've just been bitten by, I think, a red-tail fox up in Red Reef Park.
You just were bitten by a fox?
Yeah. I think he's rabid. He came out of the woods crazy.
I just killed him, though. I have him here.
You killed him?
Yeah. I chased the sucker down. He bit me and my wife both. My wife is running down the road looking for somebody, they may get another call.
He's on the phone with me, okay?
Okay. How are you feeling?
I'm all right. He bit me in the calf. He bit my wife in the knee.
Did it just come up to you and bite you?
He was growling and then he ran out of the bushes and bit my wife. Then I grabbed a stick and chased him. He bit me and then I killed him after that. He was crazy.
I don't even think it’s the only thing. We just had a raccoon attack somebody down the street too. Something's going on with the animals today.
They might have thought it was a raccoon because this guy was crazy.
Okay, yeah. Sir, stay right there in the park, okay? Don't move.
We're not at Red Reef. I'm sorry. No, no, yeah, we are. We're at Red Reef, North End.
So are you at the Red Reef Park, sir?
Red Reef Park, North End, yeah.
At the North End?
I parked in South Beach, but we're in Red Reef.
At Red Reef?
Yep. At the North End.
And this just occurred like a minute ago?
Like five minutes ago.
Yeah, I think it was the same. We have had some confusion. We'll be right there, sir. The firefighters are right down the street.
Bye-bye.
Bye.
